            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "See Poole on \"Matthew 17:14\"",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "See Poole on \"",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 17:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "\"",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and following verses to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Matthew 17:21",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Matthew 17:21",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") and considered what Mark and Luke have to complete it. For our instruction we may learn several things from the consideration of it: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1. The great goodness of God in preserving us from the power of evil spirits, as also the daily working of his providence for our preservation. What but this kept this man from being destroyed by the fires and the waters into which he had been often thrown by the evil spirit? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2. That the shorter the devil’s time is, the more he rageth, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Mark 9:20",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Mark 9:20",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". This is true, both as to the devil himself, and his instruments: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Revelation 12:12",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Revelation 12:12",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "The devil is come down unto you, having great wrath, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "because he knoweth that he hath but a short time.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Thus, in the moment of conversion Christians often meet with the strongest conflicts of temptation. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3. The fault is not in Christ, but in ourselves, if we receive not that mercy from him which he hath, and which we stand in need of, and beg from him—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (saith Christ) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "thou canst believe.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "4. God rewardeth weak faith where it is attended with a sincere desire of increase. This poor man showed a very imperfect faith in saying, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If thou canst do any thing; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " but it being in some degree sincere, the Lord rewardeth it, though weak, he desiring an increase of it, and that God would from his goodness supply what was defective in his faith. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "5. The great cures both of our bodies and souls in some cases, require more extraordinary and importunate addresses and applications unto God, more especially where evils are more inveterate. For other things relating to this history; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
